4056  ///=========================================================================
4057  /// Compute C1-curved shape functions at the local coordinate s
4058  ///========================================================================
4059  void Cshape(const Vector<double>& s, Shape& psi_curve) const
4060  {
4061  // get basis
4062  Shape basis(36);
4063  basis_curve(s, basis);
4064  // get coefficient of the basis polynomial
4065  DenseMatrix<double> A(36, 36);
4066  get_coefficient(A);
4067 
4068  Vector<double> psi(36, 0.0);
4069  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 36; i++)
4070  {
4071  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 36; j++)
4072  {
4073  psi[i] += A(i, j) * basis[j];
4074  }
4075  }
4076  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 36; i++)
4077  {
4078  psi_curve[i] = psi[i];
4079  }
4080  }
4081 
4082  ///=========================================================================
4083  /// Compute the derivatives of C1-curved shape functions at the local
4084  /// coordinate s
4085  ///=========================================================================
4086  void dCshape_local(const Vector<double>& s,
4087  Shape& psi_curve,
4088  DShape& dpsi_curve) const
4089  {
4090  Cshape(s, psi_curve);
4091  // get dbasis
4092  Shape basis(36);
4093  DShape dbasis(36, 2);
4094  dbasis_local_curve(s, basis, dbasis);
4095  // get coefficient of the basis polynomial
4096  DenseMatrix<double> A(36, 36);
4097  get_coefficient(A);
4098  DenseMatrix<double> dpsi(36, 2, 0.0);
4099  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 36; i++)
4100  {
4101  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 36; j++)
4102  {
4103  for (unsigned k = 0; k < 2; k++)
4104  {
4105  dpsi(i, k) += A(i, j) * dbasis(j, k);
4106  }
4107  }
4108  }
4109  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 36; i++)
4110  {
4111  for (unsigned k = 0; k < 2; k++)
4112  {
4113  dpsi_curve(i, k) = dpsi(i, k);
4114  }
4115  }
4116  }
4117 
4118  ///=========================================================================
4119  /// Compute the second-order derivatives of C1-curved shape functions
4120  /// at the local coordinate s
4121  ///=========================================================================
4122  void d2Cshape_local(const Vector<double>& s,
4123  Shape& psi_curve,
4124  DShape& dpsi_curve,
4125  DShape& d2psi_curve) const
4126  {
4127  dCshape_local(s, psi_curve, dpsi_curve);
4128 
4129  // get d2basis
4130  Shape basis(36);
4131  DShape dbasis(36, 2), d2basis(36, 3);
4132  d2basis_local_curve(s, basis, dbasis, d2basis);
4133  // get coefficient of the basis polynomial
4134  DenseMatrix<double> A(36, 36, 0.0);
4135  get_coefficient(A);
4136  DenseMatrix<double> d2psi(36, 3, 0.0);
4137  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 36; i++)
4138  {
4139  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 36; j++)
4140  {
4141  for (unsigned k = 0; k < 3; k++)
4142  {
4143  d2psi(i, k) += A(i, j) * d2basis(j, k);
4144  }
4145  }
4146  }
4147  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 36; i++)
4148  {
4149  for (unsigned k = 0; k < 3; k++)
4150  {
4151  d2psi_curve(i, k) = d2psi(i, k);
4152  }
4153  }
4154  }

4803  ///=========================================================================
4804  /// The second derivatived of bases of the C1-curved shape functions
4805  /// it is a complete polynomial of degree 7
4806  ///=========================================================================

4808  Shape& psi_curve,
4809  DShape& dpsi_curve,

4927  //========================================================================
4928  /// Empty base class for the subparametric Bellelements (created so that
4929  /// we can use dynamic_cast<>() to figure out if a an element
4930  /// is a C1Curvedelement). This element is sub-parametric which means
4931  /// the geometry will be parametrised by the linear Lagrange functions,
4932  /// while unknowns will be parametrised by two kinds of shape functions
4933  /// basis : denotes C1-interpolations for c1-variables
4934  /// basis_c0 : denotes C0-interpolations for c0-variables

4994  //=========================================================================
4995  /// \short Return the C1-basis function stored at the ipt-th integration
4996  /// point.
4997  //=========================================================================
4998  void basis_at_knot(const unsigned& ipt, Shape& psi) const
4999  {
5000  // Find the dimension of the element
5001  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
5002  // Storage for the local coordinates of the integration point
5003  Vector<double> s(el_dim);
5004  // Set the local coordinate
5005  for (unsigned i = 0; i < el_dim; i++)
5006  {
5007  s[i] = integral_pt()->knot(ipt, i);
5008  }
5009  // Get the shape function
5010  basis(s, psi);
5011  }
5012

5163  //=========================================================================
5164  /// Calculate the test function and its first and second derivatives
5165  /// w.r.t. local coordinates at the ipt-th integration point.

5176  Vector<double> s(el_dim);
5177  // Set the local coordinate
5178  for (unsigned i = 0; i < el_dim; i++)
5179  {
5180  s[i] = integral_pt()->knot(ipt, i);
5181  }
5182  // Get the shape function and first and second derivatives
5183  d2test_local(s, phi, dphids, d2phids);
5184  }
5185 
5186  //=========================================================================
5187  /// \short Compute the curved-element shape functions and also
5188  /// first derivatives w.r.t. local coordinates at local coordinate s;
5189  /// Returns Jacobian of mapping from global to local coordinates.
5190  /// Most general form of the function, but may be over-loaded, if desired
5191  //=========================================================================
5192  double dbasis_c0_eulerian(const Vector<double>& s,
5193  Shape& psi,
5194  DShape& dpsi) const
5195  {
5196  // Find the element dimension
5197  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
5198  // Get the values of the shape functions and their local derivatives
5199  // Temporarily stored in dpsi
5200  dbasis_c0_local(s, psi, dpsi);
5201 
5202  // assign shape functions for geometry
5203  unsigned n_node = 3;
5204  Shape psi_x(n_node);
5205  DShape dpsi_x(n_node, 2);
5206  DShape d2psi_x(n_node, 3);
5207 
5208  d2shape_local(s, psi_x, dpsi_x, d2psi_x);
5209 
5210  // Allocate memory for the jacobian and inverse jacobian
5211  DenseMatrix<double> jacobian(el_dim), inverse_jacobian(el_dim);
5212 
5213  // Calculate the jacobian and inverse jacobian
5214  const double det =
5215  this->local_to_eulerian_mapping2(dpsi_x, jacobian, inverse_jacobian);
5216 
5217  // Now set the values of the derivatives to be dpsidx
5218  transform_derivatives(inverse_jacobian, dpsi);
5219 
5220  // Return the determinant of the jacobian
5221  return det;
5222  }

5224  //===========================================================================
5225  /// \short Compute the c0-basis functions and also first
5226  /// and second derivatives w.r.t. local coordinates at ipt-th integration
5227  /// point
5228  //===========================================================================
5229  double d2basis_c0_eulerian(const Vector<double>& s,
5230  Shape& psi,
5231  DShape& dpsi,
5232  DShape& d2psi) const
5233  {
5234  // Find the element dimension
5235  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
5236  // Find the number of second derivatives required
5237  const unsigned n_deriv = N2deriv[el_dim];
5238  // Get the values of the shape function and local derivatives for unknowns
5239  d2basis_c0_local(s, psi, dpsi, d2psi);
5240 
5241  // assign shape functions for geometry
5242  unsigned n_node = 3;
5243  Shape psi_x(n_node);
5244  DShape dpsi_x(n_node, 2);
5245  DShape d2psi_x(n_node, 3);
5246 
5247  d2shape_local(s, psi_x, dpsi_x, d2psi_x);
5248 
5249  // Allocate memory for the jacobian and inverse jacobian
5250  DenseMatrix<double> jacobian(el_dim), inverse_jacobian(el_dim);
5251 
5252  // Calculate the jacobian and inverse jacobian
5253  const double det =
5254  local_to_eulerian_mapping2(dpsi_x, jacobian, inverse_jacobian);
5255 
5256  // Allocate memory for the jacobian of second derivatives
5257  DenseMatrix<double> jacobian2(n_deriv, el_dim, 0.0);
5258

5260  myassemble_local_to_eulerian_jacobian2(d2psi_x, jacobian2);
5261 
5262  // Now set the value of the derivatives
5263  transform_second_derivatives(
5264  jacobian, inverse_jacobian, jacobian2, dpsi, d2psi);
5265 
5266  // Return the determinant of the jacobian
5267  return det;
5268  }

5341  //=========================================================================
5342  /// Calculate the c0-shape function and its first-order derivatives
5343  /// w.r.t. local coordinates at the ipt-th integration point.
5344  /// \n\n Numbering:
5345  //=========================================================================
5346 
5347  double dshape_and_dtest_eulerian_at_knot(const unsigned& ipt,
5348  Shape& psi,
5349  DShape& dpsi,
5350  Shape& test,
5351  DShape& dtest) const
5352  {
5353  // Find the element dimension
5354  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
5355

5357  // and local derivatives

5359  dbasis_c0_local_at_knot(ipt, psi, dpsi);

5374

5382  //===========================================================================
5383  /// \short Compute the c1-shape functions and also first and second
5384  /// derivatives w.r.t. global coordinates at ipt-th integration points
5385  /// Returns Jacobian of mapping from global to local coordinates.
5386  //===========================================================================
5387  double d2shape_and_d2test_eulerian_at_knot(const unsigned& ipt,
5388  Shape& psi,
5389  DShape& dpsi,
5390  DShape& d2psi,
5391  Shape& test,
5392  DShape& dtest,
5393  DShape& d2test) const
5394  {
5395  // Find the element dimension
5396  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
5397 
5398  // Get the values of the shape function and local derivatives for unknowns
5399  d2basis_local_at_knot(ipt, psi, dpsi, d2psi);
5400 
5401  // assign shape functions for geometry
5402  unsigned n_node = nnode();
5403  Shape psi_x(n_node);
5404  DShape dpsi_x(n_node, 2);
5405  DShape d2psi_x(n_node, 3);
5406  dshape_local_at_knot(ipt, psi_x, dpsi_x);
5407

5413

5415  const double det =
5416  local_to_eulerian_mapping2(dpsi_x, jacobian, inverse_jacobian);

5422  //===========================================================================
5423  /// \short Calculate the mapping from local to Eulerian coordinates,
5424  /// given the derivatives of the shape functions w.r.t. local coordinates,
5425  /// Return only the determinant of the jacobian and the inverse of the
5426  /// mapping (ds/dx).
5427  //===========================================================================
5428  double local_to_eulerian_mapping2(
5429  const DShape& dpsids, DenseMatrix<double>& inverse_jacobian) const
5430  {
5431  // Find the dimension of the element
5432  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
5433  // Assign memory for the jacobian
5434  DenseMatrix<double> jacobian(el_dim);
5435  // Calculate the jacobian and inverse
5436  return local_to_eulerian_mapping2(dpsids, jacobian, inverse_jacobian);
5437  }
5438 
5439  ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5440  virtual double local_to_eulerian_mapping2(
5441  const DShape& dpsids,
5442  DenseMatrix<double>& jacobian,
5443  DenseMatrix<double>& inverse_jacobian) const
5444  {
5445  // Assemble the jacobian
5446  // Locally cache the elemental dimension
5447  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
5448  // The number of shape functions must be equal to the number
5449  // of nodes (by definition)
5450  const unsigned n_shape = 3;
5451  // The number of shape function types must be equal to the number
5452  // of nodal position types (by definition)
5453  const unsigned n_shape_type = 1;
5454 
5455  // Loop over the rows of the jacobian
5456  for (unsigned i = 0; i < el_dim; i++)
5457  {
5458  // Loop over the columns of the jacobian
5459  for (unsigned j = 0; j < el_dim; j++)
5460  {
5461  // Zero the entry
5462  jacobian(i, j) = 0.0;
5463  // Loop over the shape functions
5464  for (unsigned l = 0; l < n_shape; l++)
5465  {
5466  for (unsigned k = 0; k < n_shape_type; k++)
5467  {
5468  // Jacobian is dx_j/ds_i, which is represented by the sum
5469  // over the dpsi/ds_i of the nodal points X j
5470  // Call the Non-hanging version of positions
5471  // This is overloaded in refineable elements
5472  jacobian(i, j) +=
5473  raw_nodal_position_gen(l, k, j) * dpsids(l, k, i);
5474  }
5475  }
5476  }
5477  }
5478 
5479  // Invert the jacobian (use the template-free interface)
5480  return invert_jacobian_mapping(jacobian, inverse_jacobian);
5481  }
5482 
5483  //========================================================================
5484  /// \short Calculate the Jacobian of the mapping between local and global
5485  /// coordinates at the position s
5486  //========================================================================
5487  double J_eulerian1(const Vector<double>& s) const
5488  {
5489  // Find the number of nodes and position types
5490  const unsigned n_node = 3;
5491  const unsigned n_position_type = 1;
5492  // Find the dimension of the node and element
5493  const unsigned n_dim_node = nodal_dimension();
5494  const unsigned n_dim_element = dim();
5495 
5496 
5497  // Set up dummy memory for the shape functions
5498  Shape psi(n_node, n_position_type);
5499  DShape dpsids(n_node, n_position_type, n_dim_element);
5500  // Get the shape functions and local derivatives
5501  this->dshape_local(s, psi, dpsids);
5502 
5503  // Right calculate the base vectors
5504  DenseMatrix<double> interpolated_G(n_dim_element, n_dim_node);
5505 
5506  // Loop over the dimensions and compute the entries of the
5507  // base vector matrix
5508  for (unsigned i = 0; i < n_dim_element; i++)
5509  {
5510  for (unsigned j = 0; j < n_dim_node; j++)
5511  {
5512  // Initialise the j-th component of the i-th base vector to zero
5513  interpolated_G(i, j) = 0.0;
5514  for (unsigned l = 0; l < n_node; l++)
5515  {
5516  for (unsigned k = 0; k < n_position_type; k++)
5517  {
5518  interpolated_G(i, j) +=
5519  raw_nodal_position_gen(l, k, j) * dpsids(l, k, i);
5520  }
5521  }
5522  }
5523  }
5524 
5525  // Calculate the metric tensor of the element
5526  DenseMatrix<double> G(n_dim_element);
5527  for (unsigned i = 0; i < n_dim_element; i++)
5528  {
5529  for (unsigned j = 0; j < n_dim_element; j++)
5530  {
5531  // Initialise to zero
5532  G(i, j) = 0.0;
5533  for (unsigned k = 0; k < n_dim_node; k++)
5534  {
5535  G(i, j) += interpolated_G(i, k) * interpolated_G(j, k);
5536  }
5537  }
5538  }
5539 
5540  // Calculate the determinant of the metric tensor
5541  double det = 0.0;
5542  switch (n_dim_element)
5543  {
5544  case 0:
5545  throw OomphLibError(
5546  "Cannot calculate J_eulerian() for point element\n",
5547  "FiniteElement::J_eulerian()",
5548  OOMPH_EXCEPTION_LOCATION);
5549  break;
5550  case 1:
5551  det = G(0, 0);
5552  break;
5553  case 2:
5554  det = G(0, 0) * G(1, 1) - G(0, 1) * G(1, 0);
5555  break;
5556  case 3:
5557  det = G(0, 0) * G(1, 1) * G(2, 2) + G(0, 1) * G(1, 2) * G(2, 0) +
5558  G(0, 2) * G(1, 0) * G(2, 1) - G(0, 0) * G(1, 2) * G(2, 1) -
5559  G(0, 1) * G(1, 0) * G(2, 2) - G(0, 2) * G(1, 1) * G(2, 0);
5560  break;
5561  default:
5562  oomph_info << "More than 3 dimensions in J_eulerian()" << std::endl;
5563  break;
5564  }
5565 
5566 #ifdef PARANOID
5567  check_jacobian(det);
5568 #endif
5569 
5570  // Return the Jacobian (square-root of the determinant of the metric
5571  // tensor)
5572  return sqrt(det);
5573  }
5574 
5575  //=========================================================================
5576  /// Internal function that is used to assemble the jacobian of second
5577  /// derivatives of the the mapping from local coordinates (s) to the
5578  /// eulerian coordinates (x), given the second derivatives of the
5579  /// shape functions.
5580  //=========================================================================
5581  void myassemble_local_to_eulerian_jacobian2(
5582  const DShape& d2psids, DenseMatrix<double>& jacobian2) const
5583  {
5584  // Find the the dimension of the element
5585  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
5586  // Find the number of shape functions and shape functions types
5587  // Must be equal to the number of nodes and their position types
5588  // by the definition of the shape function.
5589  const unsigned n_shape = 3;
5590  unsigned n_shape_type = 1;
5591  // Find the number of second derivatives
5592  const unsigned n_row = N2deriv[el_dim];
5593  // Assemble the "jacobian" (d^2 x_j/ds_i^2) for second derivatives of
5594  // shape functions
5595  // Loop over the rows (number of second derivatives)
5596  for (unsigned i = 0; i < n_row; i++)
5597  {
5598  // Loop over the columns (element dimension
5599  for (unsigned j = 0; j < el_dim; j++)
5600  {
5601  // Zero the entry
5602  jacobian2(i, j) = 0.0;
5603  // Loop over the shape functions
5604  for (unsigned l = 0; l < n_shape; l++)
5605  {
5606  // Loop over the shape function types
5607  for (unsigned k = 0; k < n_shape_type; k++)
5608  {
5609  // Add the terms to the jacobian entry
5610  // Call the Non-hanging version of positions
5611  // This is overloaded in refineable elements
5612  jacobian2(i, j) +=
5613  raw_nodal_position_gen(l, k, j) * d2psids(l, k, i);
5614  }
5615  }
5616  }
5617  }
5618  }
5619 
5620  //=======================================================================
5621  /// Return FE interpolated position x[] at local coordinate s as Vector
5622  // (using linear Lagrange interpolation)
5623  //=======================================================================
5624  void my_interpolated_x(const Vector<double>& s, Vector<double>& x) const
5625  {
5626  // Find the number of nodes
5627  const unsigned n_node = 3;
5628  // Find the number of positional types
5629  const unsigned n_position_type = 1;
5630 
5631  // Find the dimension stored in the node
5632  const unsigned nodal_dim = nodal_dimension();
5633 
5634  // Assign storage for the local shape function
5635  Shape psi(n_node);
5636  // Find the values of shape function
5637  shape(s, psi);
5638 
5639  // Loop over the dimensions
5640  for (unsigned i = 0; i < nodal_dim; i++)
5641  {
5642  // Initilialise value of x[i] to zero
5643  x[i] = 0.0;
5644  // Loop over the local nodes
5645  for (unsigned l = 0; l < n_node; l++)
5646  {
5647  for (unsigned k = 0; k < n_position_type; k++)
5648  {
5649  x[i] += nodal_position_gen(l, k, i) * psi[l];
5650  }
5651  }
5652  }
5653  }
5654  };

5678  }

5707  /// \short Computer the geometric shape functions, derivatives and
5708  /// second derivatives w.r.t local coordinates at local coordinate s \n
5709  /// d2psids(i,0) = \f$ \partial^2 \psi_j / \partial s_0^2 \f$ \n
5710  /// d2psids(i,1) = \f$ \partial^2 \psi_j / \partial s_1^2 \f$ \n
5711  /// d2psids(i,2) = \f$ \partial^2 \psi_j / \partial s_0 \partial s_1 \f$ \n

5718  }

5720  /// Calculate the c1-basis functions at local coordinate s
5721  inline void basis(const Vector<double>& s, Shape& psi) const
5722  {
5723  /// Number of nodes along each element edge
5724  unsigned n_node = 3;
5725 
5726  DenseMatrix<double> node_position(n_node, DIM);
5727  for (unsigned l = 0; l < n_node; l++)
5728  {
5729  for (unsigned k = 0; k < 1; k++)
5730  {
5731  for (unsigned j = 0; j < DIM; j++)
5732  {
5733  node_position(l, j) = this->raw_nodal_position_gen(l, k, j);
5734  }
5735  }
5736  }
5737  BellElementShape<2>::Bshape(s, psi, node_position);
5738  }

5783  }
5784  }
5785  BellElementShape<2>::d2Bshape_local(
5786  s, psi, dpsids, d2psids, node_position);
5787  }

5789  /// Calculate the c0-basis functions at local coordinate s

5791  {

5793  }

5805  /// second derivatives w.r.t local coordinates at local coordinate s \n

5808  /// d2psids(i,2) = \f$ \partial^2 \psi_j / \partial s_0 \partial s_1 \f$ \n
5809  inline void d2basis_c0_local(const Vector<double>& s,
5810  Shape& psi,
5811  DShape& dpsids,
5812  DShape& d2psids) const

5815  }

5972  /// boundary stored at the ipt-th integration point.
5973  //=========================================================================

5975  {

5977  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
5978  // Storage for the local coordinates of the integration point
5979  Vector<double> s(el_dim);
5980  // Set the local coordinate
5981  for (unsigned i = 0; i < el_dim; i++)
5982  {
5983  s[i] = integral_pt()->knot(ipt, i);
5984  }
5985  // Get the shape function
5986  basis_straight(s, psi);
5987  }

6277  void d2test_local_at_knot(const unsigned& ipt,
6278  Shape& phi,
6279  DShape& dphids,
6280  DShape& d2phids) const
6281  {

6284  // Storage for the local coordinates of the integration point
6285  Vector<double> s(el_dim);

6288  {

6295  //=========================================================================
6296  /// Calculate the shape function and its first and second derivatives
6297  /// w.r.t. local coordinates at the ipt-th integration point.
6298  /// \n\n Numbering:
6299  //=========================================================================
6300  double dshape_and_dtest_eulerian_at_knot(const unsigned& ipt,
6301  Shape& psi,
6302  DShape& dpsi,
6303  Shape& test,
6304  DShape& dtest) const
6305  {
6306  // Find the element dimension
6307  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
6308  // Get the values of the shape function and local derivatives
6309  // Temporarily store it in dpsi
6310  // assign shape functions for unknowns
6311  dshape_local_at_knot(ipt, psi, dpsi);
6312 
6313  // assign shape functions for geometry -> Lagrange family
6314  unsigned n_node = 3;
6315  Shape psi_x(n_node);
6316  DShape dpsi_x(n_node, 2);
6317  Shape phi(2);
6318  DShape dphi(2, 2);
6319 
6320  // assign 'linear' shape function to geometry
6321  dshape_local_at_knot_geom(ipt, psi_x, dpsi_x, phi, dphi);
6322 
6323  // assign test function
6324  dtest_local_at_knot(ipt, test, dtest);
6325 
6326  // Allocate memory for the inverse jacobian
6327  DenseMatrix<double> jacobian(el_dim), inverse_jacobian(el_dim);
6328 
6329  // Now calculate the inverse jacobian
6330  const double det =
6331  local_to_eulerian_mapping2(dpsi_x, dphi, jacobian, inverse_jacobian);
6332 
6333  // Now set the values of the derivatives to dpsidx
6334  transform_derivatives(inverse_jacobian, dpsi);
6335 
6336  // Return the determinant of the jacobian
6337  return det;
6338  }
6339 
6340  //===========================================================================
6341  /// \short Compute the c1-shape functions that associated with the
6342  /// straight- boundary element and also first and second derivatives w.r.t.
6343  /// global coordinates at ipt-th integration point Returns Jacobian of
6344  /// mapping from global to local coordinates.
6345  //===========================================================================
6346  double d2shape_and_d2test_eulerian_at_knot(const unsigned& ipt,
6347  Shape& psi,
6348  DShape& dpsi,
6349  DShape& d2psi,
6350  Shape& test,
6351  DShape& dtest,
6352  DShape& d2test) const
6353  {
6354  // Find the values of the indices of the shape functions
6355  // Locally cached
6356  // Find the element dimension
6357  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
6358  // Get the values of the shape function and local derivatives for unknowns
6359  d2basis_local_at_knot_straight(ipt, psi, dpsi, d2psi);
6360 
6361  // assign shape functions for geometry
6362  unsigned n_node = 3;
6363  Shape psi_x(n_node);
6364  DShape dpsi_x(n_node, 2);
6365  DShape d2psi_x(n_node, 3);
6366  Shape phi(2);
6367  DShape dphi(2, 2);
6368  DShape d2phi(2, 3);
6369  d2shape_local_at_knot_geom(ipt, psi_x, dpsi_x, d2psi_x, phi, dphi, d2phi);
6370 
6371  // assign for test function
6372  d2test_local_at_knot(ipt, test, dtest, d2test);
6373 
6374  // Allocate memory for the jacobian and inverse jacobian
6375  DenseMatrix<double> jacobian(el_dim), inverse_jacobian(el_dim);
6376 
6377  // Calculate the jacobian and inverse jacobian
6378  const double det =
6379  local_to_eulerian_mapping2(dpsi_x, dphi, jacobian, inverse_jacobian);
6380 
6381  // Return the determinant of the mapping
6382  return det;
6383  }
6384 
6385  //===========================================================================
6386  /// \short Calculate the mapping from local to Eulerian coordinates,
6387  /// given the derivatives of the shape functions w.r.t. local coordinates,
6388  /// Return only the determinant of the jacobian and the inverse of the
6389  /// mapping (ds/dx).
6390  //===========================================================================
6391  double local_to_eulerian_mapping2(
6392  const DShape& dpsids,
6393  DShape& dphids,
6394  DenseMatrix<double>& inverse_jacobian) const
6395  {
6396  // Find the dimension of the element
6397  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
6398  // Assign memory for the jacobian
6399  DenseMatrix<double> jacobian(el_dim);
6400  // Calculate the jacobian and inverse
6401  return local_to_eulerian_mapping2(
6402  dpsids, dphids, jacobian, inverse_jacobian);
6403  }
6404 
6405  ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6406  virtual double local_to_eulerian_mapping2(
6407  const DShape& dpsids,
6408  DShape& dphids,
6409  DenseMatrix<double>& jacobian,
6410  DenseMatrix<double>& inverse_jacobian) const
6411  {
6412  // Assemble the jacobian
6413  // Locally cache the elemental dimension
6414  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
6415 
6416  // Loop over the rows of the jacobian
6417  for (unsigned i = 0; i < el_dim; i++)
6418  {
6419  // Loop over the columns of the jacobian
6420  for (unsigned j = 0; j < el_dim; j++)
6421  {
6422  // Zero the entry
6423  jacobian(i, j) = 0.0;
6424  jacobian(i, j) = dphids(j, i);
6425  }
6426  }
6427  // Invert the jacobian (use the template-free interface)
6428  return invert_jacobian_mapping(jacobian, inverse_jacobian);
6429  }
6430 
6431  //=========================================================================
6432  /// Internal function that is used to assemble the jacobian of second
6433  /// derivatives of the the mapping from local coordinates (s) to the
6434  /// eulerian coordinates (x), given the second derivatives of the
6435  /// shape functions.
6436  //=========================================================================
6437  void myassemble_local_to_eulerian_jacobian2(
6438  const DShape& d2psids, DenseMatrix<double>& jacobian2) const
6439  {
6440  // Find the the dimension of the element
6441  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
6442  // Find the number of second derivatives
6443  const unsigned n_row = N2deriv[el_dim];
6444  // Assemble the "jacobian" (d^2 x_j/ds_i^2) for second derivatives of
6445  // shape functions
6446  // Loop over the rows (number of second derivatives)
6447  for (unsigned i = 0; i < n_row; i++)
6448  {
6449  // Loop over the columns (element dimension
6450  for (unsigned j = 0; j < el_dim; j++)
6451  {
6452  // Zero the entry
6453  jacobian2(i, j) = 0.0;
6454  jacobian2(i, j) = d2psids(j, i);
6455  }
6456  }
6457  }
6458 
6459  //=======================================================================
6460  /// Return FE interpolated position x[] at local coordinate s as Vector
6461  // (using Hermite interpolation)
6462  //=======================================================================
6463  void my_interpolated_x(const Vector<double>& s, Vector<double>& x) const
6464  {
6465  // Find the number of nodes
6466  const unsigned n_node = 3;
6467  // Assign storage for the local shape function
6468  Shape psi(n_node);
6469  Shape phi(2);
6470  // Find the values of shape function
6471  shape_geom(s, psi, phi);
6472 
6473  x[0] = phi[0];
6474  x[1] = phi[1];
6475  }
6476 
6477  //========================================================================
6478  /// \short Calculate the Jacobian of the mapping between local and global
6479  /// coordinates at the position s
6480  //========================================================================
6481  double J_eulerian1(const Vector<double>& s) const
6482  {
6483  // Find the number of nodes and position types
6484  const unsigned n_node = 3;
6485  // Find the dimension of the node and element
6486  const unsigned n_dim_node = this->nodal_dimension();
6487  const unsigned n_dim_element = this->dim();
6488 
6489  // Set up dummy memory for the shape functions
6490  // compute the jacobian of mapping matrix
6491  Shape psi(n_node), phi(2);
6492  DShape dpsids(n_node, n_dim_element), dphi(2, 2);
6493  // Get the shape functions and local derivatives for geometry
6494  this->dshape_local_geom(s, psi, dpsids, phi, dphi);
6495 
6496  // Right calculate the base vectors
6497  DenseMatrix<double> interpolated_G(n_dim_element, n_dim_node);
6498 
6499  // Loop over the dimensions and compute the entries of the
6500  // base vector matrix
6501  for (unsigned i = 0; i < n_dim_element; i++)
6502  {
6503  for (unsigned j = 0; j < n_dim_node; j++)
6504  {
6505  interpolated_G(i, j) = dphi(j, i);
6506  }
6507  }
6508 
6509  // Calculate the metric tensor of the element
6510  DenseMatrix<double> G(n_dim_element);
6511  for (unsigned i = 0; i < n_dim_element; i++)
6512  {
6513  for (unsigned j = 0; j < n_dim_element; j++)
6514  {
6515  // Initialise to zero
6516  G(i, j) = 0.0;
6517  for (unsigned k = 0; k < n_dim_node; k++)
6518  {
6519  G(i, j) += interpolated_G(i, k) * interpolated_G(j, k);
6520  }
6521  }
6522  }
6523 
6524  // Calculate the determinant of the metric tensor
6525  double det = 0.0;
6526  switch (n_dim_element)
6527  {
6528  case 0:
6529  throw OomphLibError(
6530  "Cannot calculate J_eulerian() for point element\n",
6531  "FiniteElement::J_eulerian()",
6532  OOMPH_EXCEPTION_LOCATION);
6533  break;
6534  case 1:
6535  det = G(0, 0);
6536  break;
6537  case 2:
6538  det = G(0, 0) * G(1, 1) - G(0, 1) * G(1, 0);
6539  break;
6540  case 3:
6541  det = G(0, 0) * G(1, 1) * G(2, 2) + G(0, 1) * G(1, 2) * G(2, 0) +
6542  G(0, 2) * G(1, 0) * G(2, 1) - G(0, 0) * G(1, 2) * G(2, 1) -
6543  G(0, 1) * G(1, 0) * G(2, 2) - G(0, 2) * G(1, 1) * G(2, 0);
6544  break;
6545  default:
6546  oomph_info << "More than 3 dimensions in J_eulerian()" << std::endl;
6547  break;
6548  }
6549 
6550 #ifdef PARANOID
6551  this->check_jacobian(det);
6552 #endif
6553 
6554  // Return the Jacobian (square-root of the determinant of the metric
6555  // tensor)
6556  return det;
6557  }
6558 
6559  // =======================================================================
6560  // Check whether this element is a boundary element or not
6561  //========================================================================
6562  unsigned is_boundary_element() const
6563  {
6564  unsigned n_node = 3;
6565  int count = 0;
6566  // check whether this element is on boundary or not
6567  for (unsigned i = 0; i < n_node; i++)
6568  {
6569  // check whether this node is on 1st boundary (curve boundary)
6570  bool bd_node1 = node_pt(i)->is_on_boundary(1);
6571  if (bd_node1 == 1)
6572  {
6573  count += 1;
6574  }
6575  }
6576  unsigned bd_element;
6577  if (count == 2)
6578  {
6579  bd_element = 1;
6580  }
6581  else
6582  {
6583  bd_element = 0;
6584  }
6585  return bd_element;
6586  }

6588  //=========================================================================
6589  /// \short Compute the c0-shape functions and also
6590  /// first derivatives w.r.t. global coordinates at local coordinate s;
6591  /// Returns Jacobian of mapping from global to local coordinates.
6592  /// Most general form of the function, but may be over-loaded, if desired
6593  //=========================================================================
6594  double dbasis_c0_eulerian(const Vector<double>& s,
6595  Shape& psi,
6596  DShape& dpsi) const
6597  {
6598  // Find the element dimension
6599  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
6600  // Get the values of the shape functions and their local derivatives
6601  // Temporarily stored in dpsi
6602  dbasis_c0_local(s, psi, dpsi);
6603 
6604  // assign shape functions for geometry
6605  unsigned n_node = 3;
6606  Shape psi_x(n_node);
6607  DShape dpsi_x(n_node, 2);
6608  DShape d2psi_x(n_node, 3);
6609  Shape phi(2);
6610  DShape dphi(2, 2);
6611  DShape d2phi(2, 3);
6612  d2shape_local_geom(s, psi_x, dpsi_x, d2psi_x, phi, dphi, d2phi);
6613 
6614  // Allocate memory for the jacobian and inverse jacobian
6615  DenseMatrix<double> jacobian(el_dim), inverse_jacobian(el_dim);
6616  // Calculate the jacobian and inverse jacobian
6617  const double det = this->local_to_eulerian_mapping2(
6618  dpsi_x, dphi, jacobian, inverse_jacobian);
6619  // Now set the values of the derivatives to be dpsidx
6620  transform_derivatives(inverse_jacobian, dpsi);
6621  // Return the determinant of the jacobian
6622  return det;
6623  }
6624 
6625  //=========================================================================
6626  /// \short Compute the c0-shape functions and also the first and the
6627  /// second derivatives w.r.t.global coordinates at local coordinate s;
6628  /// Returns Jacobian of mapping from global to local coordinates.
6629  /// Most general form of the function, but may be over-loaded, if desired
6630  //=========================================================================
6631  double d2basis_c0_eulerian(const Vector<double>& s,
6632  Shape& psi,
6633  DShape& dpsi,
6634  DShape& d2psi) const
6635  {
6636  // Find the element dimension
6637  const unsigned el_dim = dim();
6638  // Find the number of second derivatives required
6639  const unsigned n_deriv = N2deriv[el_dim];
6640  // Get the values of the shape function and local derivatives for unknowns
6641  d2basis_c0_local(s, psi, dpsi, d2psi);
6642 
6643  // assign shape functions for geometry
6644  unsigned n_node = 3;
6645  Shape psi_x(n_node);
6646  DShape dpsi_x(n_node, 2);
6647  DShape d2psi_x(n_node, 3);
6648  Shape phi(2);
6649  DShape dphi(2, 2);
6650  DShape d2phi(2, 3);
6651  d2shape_local_geom(s, psi_x, dpsi_x, d2psi_x, phi, dphi, d2phi);
6652 
6653  // Allocate memory for the jacobian and inverse jacobian
6654  DenseMatrix<double> jacobian(el_dim), inverse_jacobian(el_dim);
6655  // Calculate the jacobian and inverse jacobian
6656  const double det =
6657  local_to_eulerian_mapping2(dpsi_x, dphi, jacobian, inverse_jacobian);
6658  // Allocate memory for the jacobian of second derivatives
6659  DenseMatrix<double> jacobian2(n_deriv, el_dim, 0.0);
6660  // Assemble the jacobian of second derivatives
6661  myassemble_local_to_eulerian_jacobian2(d2phi, jacobian2);
6662  // Now set the value of the derivatives
6663  transform_second_derivatives(
6664  jacobian, inverse_jacobian, jacobian2, dpsi, d2psi);
6665  // Return the determinant of the jacobian
6666  return det;
6667  }

6749  //=======================================================================
6750  /// Return raw nodal value for nodes specified on the reference triangle
6751  //=======================================================================
6752  void get_nodal_value_curve1(Vector<double>& u_value, DenseMatrix<double>& M)
6753  {
6754  // assign degrees of freedom to the reference element
6755  DenseMatrix<double> D(21, 21), B(21, 36);
6756  Vector<double> temp(21, 0.0);
6757  DenseMatrix<double> position(3, 2);
6758  unsigned bd_element;
6759  DenseMatrix<double> bd_position(20, 2);
6760  Vector<double> x(2);
6761 
6762  // Get the nodal values of the unknown
6763  Vector<double> value(21);
6764 
6765  value[0] = raw_nodal_value(0, 0);
6766  value[1] = raw_nodal_value(1, 0);
6767  value[2] = raw_nodal_value(2, 0);
6768  value[3] = raw_nodal_value(0, 1);
6769  value[4] = raw_nodal_value(0, 2);
6770  value[5] = raw_nodal_value(1, 1);
6771  value[6] = raw_nodal_value(1, 2);
6772  value[7] = raw_nodal_value(2, 1);
6773  value[8] = raw_nodal_value(2, 2);
6774  value[9] = raw_nodal_value(0, 3);
6775  value[10] = raw_nodal_value(0, 5);
6776  value[11] = raw_nodal_value(0, 4);
6777  value[12] = raw_nodal_value(1, 3);
6778  value[13] = raw_nodal_value(1, 5);
6779  value[14] = raw_nodal_value(1, 4);
6780  value[15] = raw_nodal_value(2, 3);
6781  value[16] = raw_nodal_value(2, 5);
6782  value[17] = raw_nodal_value(2, 4);
6783  value[18] = raw_nodal_value(3, 0);
6784  value[19] = raw_nodal_value(4, 0);
6785  value[20] = raw_nodal_value(5, 0);
6786 
6787  // Transformation metrix associating nodal values between the reference
6788  // and the physical curved triangle
6789  get_value_transform_matrix(D, B, position, bd_element, bd_position, x);
6790 
6791  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 21; i++)
6792  {
6793  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 36; j++)
6794  {
6795  for (unsigned k = 0; k < 21; k++)
6796  {
6797  M(i, j) += D(i, k) * B(k, j);
6798  }
6799  }
6800  }
6801 
6802  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 21; i++)
6803  {
6804  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 21; j++)
6805  {
6806  // get values wrt local coordinates
6807  temp[i] += value[j] * D(j, i);
6808  }
6809  }
6810 
6811  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 36; i++)
6812  {
6813  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 21; j++)
6814  {
6815  u_value[i] += temp[j] * B(j, i);
6816  }
6817  }
6818  }
6819 
6820  //=======================================================================
6821  /// Return raw nodal equations for nodes specified on the curved triangle
6822  /// This function will be employed for the post-permutation as
6823  /// the nodal values defined on the element doesn't match with the defined
6824  /// shape functions
6825  //=======================================================================
6826  void get_nodal_eqn_curve(DenseMatrix<int>& nodal_eqn)
6827  {
6828  // assign degrees of freedom to the reference element
6829  DenseMatrix<double> D(21, 21), B(21, 36);
6830  DenseMatrix<double> position(3, 2);
6831  unsigned bd_element;
6832  DenseMatrix<double> bd_position(20, 2);
6833  Vector<double> x(2);
6834  unsigned n_position_type = 6;
6835 
6836  // Get nodal values at nodes on the reference element
6837  get_value_transform_matrix(D, B, position, bd_element, bd_position, x);
6838 
6839  double angle_1 = atan(bd_position(0, 1) / bd_position(0, 0));
6840  double angle_2 = atan(bd_position(1, 1) / bd_position(1, 0));
6841  if (angle_1 > angle_2)
6842  {
6843  for (unsigned k = 0; k < n_position_type; k++)
6844  {
6845  unsigned i = 2 + k;
6846  nodal_eqn(0, k) = nodal_local_eqn(2, i);
6847  nodal_eqn(1, k) = nodal_local_eqn(0, i);
6848  nodal_eqn(2, k) = nodal_local_eqn(1, i);
6849  nodal_eqn(3, k) = nodal_local_eqn(5, i);
6850  nodal_eqn(4, k) = nodal_local_eqn(3, i);
6851  nodal_eqn(5, k) = nodal_local_eqn(4, i);
6852  nodal_eqn(nnode() - 3, k) = nodal_local_eqn(nnode() - 3, i);
6853  nodal_eqn(nnode() - 2, k) = nodal_local_eqn(nnode() - 2, i);
6854  nodal_eqn(nnode() - 1, k) = nodal_local_eqn(nnode() - 1, i);
6855  }
6856  }
6857  else if (angle_1 < angle_2)
6858  {
6859  if (position(0, 0) == bd_position(0, 0) &&
6860  position(0, 1) == bd_position(0, 1))
6861  {
6862  for (unsigned k = 0; k < n_position_type; k++)
6863  {
6864  nodal_eqn(0, k) = nodal_local_eqn(0, 2 + k);
6865  nodal_eqn(1, k) = nodal_local_eqn(1, 2 + k);
6866  nodal_eqn(2, k) = nodal_local_eqn(2, 2 + k);
6867  nodal_eqn(3, k) = nodal_local_eqn(3, 2 + k);
6868  nodal_eqn(4, k) = nodal_local_eqn(4, 2 + k);
6869  nodal_eqn(5, k) = nodal_local_eqn(5, 2 + k);
6870  nodal_eqn(nnode() - 3, k) = nodal_local_eqn(nnode() - 2, 2 + k);
6871  nodal_eqn(nnode() - 2, k) = nodal_local_eqn(nnode() - 1, 2 + k);
6872  nodal_eqn(nnode() - 1, k) = nodal_local_eqn(nnode() - 3, 2 + k);
6873  }
6874  }
6875  else
6876  {
6877  for (unsigned k = 0; k < n_position_type; k++)
6878  {
6879  nodal_eqn(0, k) = nodal_local_eqn(1, 2 + k);
6880  nodal_eqn(1, k) = nodal_local_eqn(2, 2 + k);
6881  nodal_eqn(2, k) = nodal_local_eqn(0, 2 + k);
6882  nodal_eqn(3, k) = nodal_local_eqn(4, 2 + k);
6883  nodal_eqn(4, k) = nodal_local_eqn(5, 2 + k);
6884  nodal_eqn(5, k) = nodal_local_eqn(3, 2 + k);
6885  nodal_eqn(nnode() - 3, k) = nodal_local_eqn(nnode() - 1, 2 + k);
6886  nodal_eqn(nnode() - 2, k) = nodal_local_eqn(nnode() - 3, 2 + k);
6887  nodal_eqn(nnode() - 1, k) = nodal_local_eqn(nnode() - 2, 2 + k);
6888  }
6889  }
6890  }
6891  }
6892 
6893  //=======================================================================
6894  /// Return FE interpolated value u[] at local coordinate s as Vector
6895  /// using Bell interpolations for the straight-edges triangle
6896  /// using C1-curved interpolations for the curve-edges triangle
6897  // This one is for the pre-permutation
6898  //=======================================================================
6899  void my_interpolated_u_normal1(const Vector<double> s,
6900  Vector<double>& interpolated_u,
6901  DenseMatrix<double>& interpolated_dudxi,
6902  DenseMatrix<double>& interpolated_d2udxi,
6903  DenseMatrix<double>& M)
6904  {
6905  // To check whether this element is on the boundary
6906  unsigned bd_element = is_boundary_element();
6907  // Find the number of positional types
6908  const unsigned n_position_type = nnodal_position_type();
6909  if (bd_element == 0)
6910  {
6911  // Assign storage for the local shape function
6912  Shape psi(3, 6);
6913  DShape dpsi(3, 6, 2), d2psi(3, 6, 3);
6914 
6915  // Assign shape functions and their derivatives
6916  d2basis_local_straight(s, psi, dpsi, d2psi);
6917 
6918  // Loop over nodes
6919  for (unsigned l = 0; l < 3; l++)
6920  {
6921  for (unsigned k = 0; k < n_position_type; k++)
6922  {
6923  // Get the nodal value of the unknown
6924  double u_val = raw_nodal_value(l, k);
6925  interpolated_u[0] += u_val * psi(l, k);
6926 
6927  // Loop over directions
6928  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 2; j++)
6929  {
6930  interpolated_dudxi(0, j) += u_val * dpsi(l, k, j);
6931  }
6932  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 3; j++)
6933  {
6934  interpolated_d2udxi(0, j) += u_val * d2psi(l, k, j);
6935  }
6936  }
6937  }
6938  }
6939  // if it is the boundary element
6940  else if (bd_element == 1)
6941  {
6942  Vector<double> u_value(36, 0.0);
6943  // Get nodal values at nodes on the reference element
6944  get_nodal_value_curve1(u_value, M);
6945 
6946  // Assign storage for the local shape functio to a curved element
6947  Shape psi_curve(36), basis(36);
6948  DShape dpsi_curve(36, 2), d2psi_curve(36, 3), dbasis(36, 2),
6949  d2basis(36, 3);
6950 
6951  // derivative have to be wrt global coor.
6952  d2basis_eulerian_curve(s, psi_curve, dpsi_curve, d2psi_curve);
6953  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 36; i++)
6954  {
6955  interpolated_u[0] += u_value[i] * psi_curve[i];
6956  // Loop over directions
6957  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 2; j++)
6958  {
6959  interpolated_dudxi(0, j) += u_value[i] * dpsi_curve(i, j);
6960  }
6961  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 3; j++)
6962  {
6963  interpolated_d2udxi(0, j) += u_value[i] * d2psi_curve(i, j);
6964  }
6965  }
6966  }
6967  }
6968 
6969  //=======================================================================
6970  /// Return FE interpolated value u[] at local coordinate s as Vector
6971  /// using Bell interpolations for the straight-edges triangle
6972  /// using C1-curved interpolations for the curve-edges triangle
6973  // This one is for post-permutation
6974  //=======================================================================
6975  void my_interpolated_u_normal(
6976  const Vector<double> s,
6977  Vector<double>& interpolated_u,
6978  DenseMatrix<double>& interpolated_dudxi,
6979  DenseMatrix<double>& interpolated_d2udxi) const
6980  {
6981  // To check whether this element is on the boundary
6982  unsigned bd_element = is_boundary_element();
6983 
6984  // Find the number of positional types
6985  const unsigned n_position_type = nnodal_position_type();
6986 
6987  if (bd_element == 0)
6988  {
6989  // Assign storage for the local shape function
6990  Shape psi(3, 6);
6991  DShape dpsi(3, 6, 2), d2psi(3, 6, 3);
6992  // Assign shape functions and their derivatives
6993  d2basis_local_straight(s, psi, dpsi, d2psi);
6994 
6995  // Loop over nodes
6996  for (unsigned l = 0; l < 3; l++)
6997  {
6998  for (unsigned k = 0; k < n_position_type; k++)
6999  {
7000  // Get the nodal value of the poisson unknown
7001  double u_val = raw_nodal_value(l, 2 + k);
7002  interpolated_u[0] += u_val * psi(l, k);
7003  // Loop over directions
7004  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 2; j++)
7005  {
7006  interpolated_dudxi(0, j) += u_val * dpsi(l, k, j);
7007  }
7008  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 3; j++)
7009  {
7010  interpolated_d2udxi(0, j) += u_val * d2psi(l, k, j);
7011  }
7012  }
7013  }
7014  }
7015  // if it is the boundary element
7016  else if (bd_element == 1)
7017  {
7018  // assign degrees of freedom to the reference element
7019  DenseMatrix<double> D(21, 21), B(21, 36);
7020  Vector<double> temp(21, 0.0);
7021  Vector<double> u_value(36, 0.0);
7022  DenseMatrix<double> position(3, 2);
7023  unsigned bd_element;
7024  DenseMatrix<double> bd_position(20, 2);
7025  Vector<double> x(2);
7026  // Get nodal values at nodes on the reference element
7027  get_value_transform_matrix(D, B, position, bd_element, bd_position, x);
7028 
7029  Vector<double> value(21);
7030 
7031  double angle_1 = atan(bd_position(0, 1) / bd_position(0, 0));
7032  double angle_2 = atan(bd_position(1, 1) / bd_position(1, 0));
7033  if (angle_1 > angle_2)
7034  {
7035  DenseMatrix<double> nodal_value(3, n_position_type);
7036  for (unsigned k = 0; k < n_position_type; k++)
7037  {
7038  nodal_value(0, k) = raw_nodal_value(2, 2 + k);
7039  nodal_value(1, k) = raw_nodal_value(0, 2 + k);
7040  nodal_value(2, k) = raw_nodal_value(1, 2 + k);
7041  }
7042  value[0] = nodal_value(0, 0);
7043  value[1] = nodal_value(1, 0);
7044  value[2] = nodal_value(2, 0);
7045  value[3] = nodal_value(0, 1);
7046  value[4] = nodal_value(0, 2);
7047  value[5] = nodal_value(1, 1);
7048  value[6] = nodal_value(1, 2);
7049  value[7] = nodal_value(2, 1);
7050  value[8] = nodal_value(2, 2);
7051  value[9] = nodal_value(0, 3);
7052  value[10] = nodal_value(0, 5);
7053  value[11] = nodal_value(0, 4);
7054  value[12] = nodal_value(1, 3);
7055  value[13] = nodal_value(1, 5);
7056  value[14] = nodal_value(1, 4);
7057  value[15] = nodal_value(2, 3);
7058  value[16] = nodal_value(2, 5);
7059  value[17] = nodal_value(2, 4);
7060  value[18] = raw_nodal_value(nnode() - 3, 2 + 0);
7061  value[19] = raw_nodal_value(nnode() - 2, 2 + 0);
7062  value[20] = raw_nodal_value(nnode() - 1, 2 + 0);
7063  }
7064  else if (angle_1 < angle_2)
7065  {
7066  if (position(0, 0) == bd_position(0, 0) &&
7067  position(0, 1) == bd_position(0, 1))
7068  {
7069  value[0] = raw_nodal_value(0, 2 + 0);
7070  value[1] = raw_nodal_value(1, 2 + 0);
7071  value[2] = raw_nodal_value(2, 2 + 0);
7072  value[3] = raw_nodal_value(0, 2 + 1);
7073  value[4] = raw_nodal_value(0, 2 + 2);
7074  value[5] = raw_nodal_value(1, 2 + 1);
7075  value[6] = raw_nodal_value(1, 2 + 2);
7076  value[7] = raw_nodal_value(2, 2 + 1);
7077  value[8] = raw_nodal_value(2, 2 + 2);
7078  value[9] = raw_nodal_value(0, 2 + 3);
7079  value[10] = raw_nodal_value(0, 2 + 5);
7080  value[11] = raw_nodal_value(0, 2 + 4);
7081  value[12] = raw_nodal_value(1, 2 + 3);
7082  value[13] = raw_nodal_value(1, 2 + 5);
7083  value[14] = raw_nodal_value(1, 2 + 4);
7084  value[15] = raw_nodal_value(2, 2 + 3);
7085  value[16] = raw_nodal_value(2, 2 + 5);
7086  value[17] = raw_nodal_value(2, 2 + 4);
7087  value[18] = raw_nodal_value(nnode() - 2, 2 + 0);
7088  value[19] = raw_nodal_value(nnode() - 1, 2 + 0);
7089  value[20] = raw_nodal_value(nnode() - 3, 2 + 0);
7090  }
7091  else
7092  {
7093  DenseMatrix<double> nodal_value(3, n_position_type);
7094  for (unsigned k = 0; k < n_position_type; k++)
7095  {
7096  nodal_value(2, k) = raw_nodal_value(0, 2 + k);
7097  nodal_value(0, k) = raw_nodal_value(1, 2 + k);
7098  nodal_value(1, k) = raw_nodal_value(2, 2 + k);
7099  }
7100  value[0] = nodal_value(0, 0);
7101  value[1] = nodal_value(1, 0);
7102  value[2] = nodal_value(2, 0);
7103  value[3] = nodal_value(0, 1);
7104  value[4] = nodal_value(0, 2);
7105  value[5] = nodal_value(1, 1);
7106  value[6] = nodal_value(1, 2);
7107  value[7] = nodal_value(2, 1);
7108  value[8] = nodal_value(2, 2);
7109  value[9] = nodal_value(0, 3);
7110  value[10] = nodal_value(0, 5);
7111  value[11] = nodal_value(0, 4);
7112  value[12] = nodal_value(1, 3);
7113  value[13] = nodal_value(1, 5);
7114  value[14] = nodal_value(1, 4);
7115  value[15] = nodal_value(2, 3);
7116  value[16] = nodal_value(2, 5);
7117  value[17] = nodal_value(2, 4);
7118  value[18] = raw_nodal_value(nnode() - 1, 2 + 0);
7119  value[19] = raw_nodal_value(nnode() - 3, 2 + 0);
7120  value[20] = raw_nodal_value(nnode() - 2, 2 + 0);
7121  }
7122  }
7123 
7124  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 21; i++)
7125  {
7126  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 21; j++)
7127  {
7128  // get values wrt local coordinates
7129  temp[i] += value[j] * D(j, i);
7130  }
7131  }
7132 
7133  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 36; i++)
7134  {
7135  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 21; j++)
7136  {
7137  u_value[i] += temp[j] * B(j, i);
7138  }
7139  }
7140 
7141  // Assign storage for the local shape functio to a curved element
7142  Shape psi_curve(36), basis(36);
7143  DShape dpsi_curve(36, 2), d2psi_curve(36, 3), dbasis(36, 2),
7144  d2basis(36, 3);
7145  // derivative have to be wrt global coor.
7146  d2basis_eulerian_curve(s, psi_curve, dpsi_curve, d2psi_curve);
7147 
7148  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 36; i++)
7149  {
7150  interpolated_u[0] += u_value[i] * psi_curve[i];
7151  // Loop over directions
7152  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 2; j++)
7153  {
7154  interpolated_dudxi(0, j) += u_value[i] * dpsi_curve(i, j);
7155  }
7156  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 3; j++)
7157  {
7158  interpolated_d2udxi(0, j) += u_value[i] * d2psi_curve(i, j);
7159  }
7160  }
7161  }
7162  }
7163 
7164  //=======================================================================
7165  /// Return FE interpolated value u[] at local coordinate s as Vector
7166  // (using Lagrange interpolations)
7167  //=======================================================================
7168  void my_interpolated_u_tangential(
7169  const Vector<double> s,
7170  Vector<double>& interpolated_u,
7171  DenseMatrix<double>& interpolated_dudxi) const
7172  {
7173  unsigned n_node = nnode() - 3;
7174 
7175  // Local shape function
7176  Shape psi(n_node);
7177  DShape dpsi(n_node, 2);
7178  this->dbasis_c0_eulerian(s, psi, dpsi);
7179 
7180  // Interpolated in tangential direction
7181  for (unsigned l = 0; l < n_node; l++)
7182  {
7183  interpolated_u[0] += this->raw_nodal_value(l, 0) * psi[l];
7184  interpolated_u[1] += this->raw_nodal_value(l, 1) * psi[l];
7185  // Loop over directions
7186  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 2; j++)
7187  {
7188  interpolated_dudxi(0, j) += this->raw_nodal_value(l, 0) * dpsi(l, j);
7189  interpolated_dudxi(1, j) += this->raw_nodal_value(l, 1) * dpsi(l, j);
7190  }
7191  }
7192  }
7193  };
7194 
7195  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7196  /// General C1CurvedElement class ///
7197  /// Empty, just establishes the template parameters
7198  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7199  template<unsigned DIM, unsigned NNODE_1D>
7200  class C1CurvedElement
7201  {
7202  };
7203 
7204  //=======================================================================
7205  /// C1CurvedElement elements, specialised to two spatial dimensions
7206  //=======================================================================
7207  template<unsigned NNODE_1D>
7208  class C1CurvedElement<2, NNODE_1D>
7209  : public virtual C1CurvedElementBase<NNODE_1D>,
7210  public virtual TElement<2, NNODE_1D>,
7211  public virtual GeometricTElement<2>,
7212  public virtual C1CurvedElementShape<2, NNODE_1D>,
7213  public virtual BellElementShape<2>
7214  {
7215  private:
7216  /// Nodal translation scheme for use when generating face elements
7217  static const unsigned NodeOnFace[3][NNODE_1D];
7218 
7219  public:
7220  ///\short Constructor: Call constructors for C1CurvedElement
7221  C1CurvedElement()
7222  : C1CurvedElementBase<NNODE_1D>(),
7223  TElement<2, NNODE_1D>(),
7224  GeometricTElement<2>(),
7225  C1CurvedElementShape<2, NNODE_1D>(),
7226  BellElementShape<2>()
7227  {
7228  // Number of nodes
7229  switch (NNODE_1D)
7230  {
7231  case 2:
7232  case 3:
7233  break;
7234 
7235  default:
7236  std::string error_message =
7237  "Triangles are currently only implemented for\n";
7238  error_message +=
7239  "three vertices and three internal nodes, i.e. NNODE_1D=2,3 only\n";
7240 
7241  throw OomphLibError(error_message,
7242  "CurvedTElement::CurvedTElement()",
7243  OOMPH_EXCEPTION_LOCATION);
7244  }
7245 
7246  // Set the number of nodes
7247  unsigned n_node = (NNODE_1D * (NNODE_1D + 1)) / 2 + 3;
7248  this->set_n_node(n_node);
7249  // Set the elemental and nodal dimension
7250  this->set_dimension(2);
7251  // Set the number of types required to interpolate the coordinate
7252  this->set_nnodal_position_type(6);
7253  TGauss<2, 5>* new_integral_pt = new TGauss<2, 5>;
7254  this->set_integration_scheme(new_integral_pt);
7255  }
7256

7258  C1CurvedElement(const C1CurvedElement&)
7259  {
7260  BrokenCopy::broken_copy("C1CurvedElement");
7261  }
7262 
7263  /// Broken assignment operator
7264  void operator=(const C1CurvedElement&)
7265  {
7266  BrokenCopy::broken_assign("C1CurvedElement");
7267  }

7269  ~C1CurvedElement() {}

7272  unsigned nnode_1d() const
7273  {
7274  return NNODE_1D;
7275  }
7276

7278  /// than spatial dimension
7279  unsigned nvertex_node() const
7280  {
7281  return 3;
7282  }
7283 
7284  /// Number of internal nodes
7285  unsigned ninternal_node() const
7286  {
7287  return 3;
7288  }
7289 
7290  /// \short Pointer to the j-th vertex node in the element
7291  Node* vertex_node_pt(const unsigned& j) const
7292  {
7293  // Vertex nodes come first:
7294 #ifdef PARANOID
7295  if (j > 2)
7296  {
7297  std::ostringstream error_message;
7298  error_message
7299  << "Element only has three vertex nodes; called with node number "
7300  << j << std::endl;
7301  throw OomphLibError(error_message.str(),
7302  "TElement::vertex_node_pt()",
7303  OOMPH_EXCEPTION_LOCATION);
7304  }
7305 #endif
7306  return this->node_pt(j);
7307  }
7308 
7309  // Classify nodes on the element: boundary nodes and non-boundary nodes
7310  inline void classify_boundary_node(DenseMatrix<double>& node_position,
7311  unsigned& bd_element,
7312  DenseMatrix<double>& bd_node_position,
7313  Vector<double>& x) const
7314  {
7315  /// Number of nodes along each element edge: Just for the three vertices
7316  /// not the internal points
7317  unsigned n_node = 3;
7318  /// Loop over vertices
7319  for (unsigned l = 0; l < n_node; l++)
7320  {
7321  for (unsigned k = 0; k < 1; k++)
7322  {
7323  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 2; j++)
7324  {
7325  node_position(l, j) = this->raw_nodal_position_gen(l, k, j);
7326  }
7327  }
7328  }
7329 
7330  int count = 0;
7331 
7332  // check whether this element is on boundary or not
7333  for (unsigned i = 0; i < n_node; i++)
7334  {
7335  // check whether this node is on 1st boundary (curve boundary)
7336  bool bd_node1 = this->node_pt(i)->is_on_boundary(1);
7337  if (bd_node1 == 1)
7338  {
7339  count += 1;
7340  for (unsigned k = 0; k < 1; k++)
7341  {
7342  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 2; j++)
7343  {
7344  bd_node_position(count - 1, j) =
7345  this->raw_nodal_position_gen(i, k, j);
7346  }
7347  }
7348  }
7349  else
7350  {
7351  for (unsigned k = 0; k < 1; k++)
7352  {
7353  for (unsigned j = 0; j < 2; j++)
7354  {
7355  x[j] = this->raw_nodal_position_gen(i, k, j);
7356  }
7357  }
7358  }
7359  }
7360  if (count == 2) // this case is a boundary element
7361  {
7362  bd_element = 1;
7363  }
7364  else
7365  {
7366  bd_element = 0;
7367  }
7368  }
7369 
7370  // assign the set of value for a curved element
7371  inline void get_value_transform_matrix(
7372  DenseMatrix<double>& D,
7373  DenseMatrix<double>& B,
7374  DenseMatrix<double>& node_position,
7375  unsigned& bd_element,
7376  DenseMatrix<double>& bd_node_position,
7377  Vector<double>& x) const
7378  {
7379  /// classify nodes in the element
7380  classify_boundary_node(node_position, bd_element, bd_node_position, x);
7381  /// compute the set of value of degree of freedom
7382  C1CurvedElementShape<2, NNODE_1D>::set_of_value(
7383  D, B, node_position, bd_element, bd_node_position, x);
7384  }

7391  }

7540 
7541  /// \short Compute the c0-shape functions and
7542  /// derivatives w.r.t. local coordinates at local coordinate s
7543  inline void dbasis_c0_local(const Vector<double>& s,
7544  Shape& psi,
7545  DShape& dpsids) const
7546  {
7547  TElementShape<2, NNODE_1D>::dshape_local(s, psi, dpsids);
7548  }
7549 
7550  /// \short Computer the c0-shape functions, derivatives and
7551  /// second derivatives w.r.t local coordinates at local coordinate s \n
7552  /// d2psids(i,0) = \f$ \partial^2 \psi_j / \partial s_0^2 \f$ \n
7553  /// d2psids(i,1) = \f$ \partial^2 \psi_j / \partial s_1^2 \f$ \n
7554  /// d2psids(i,2) = \f$ \partial^2 \psi_j / \partial s_0 \partial s_1 \f$ \n
7555  inline void d2basis_c0_local(const Vector<double>& s,
7556  Shape& psi,
7557  DShape& dpsids,
7558  DShape& d2psids) const
7559  {
7560  TElementShape<2, NNODE_1D>::d2shape_local(s, psi, dpsids, d2psids);
7561  }
7562 
7563  /// Calculate the test functions at local coordinate s
7564  inline void test(const Vector<double>& s, Shape& psi) const
7565  {
7566  TElementShape<2, NNODE_1D>::shape(s, psi);
7567  }
7568 
7569  /// \short Compute the test functions and
7570  /// derivatives w.r.t. local coordinates at local coordinate s
7571  inline void dtest_local(const Vector<double>& s,
7572  Shape& psi,
7573  DShape& dpsids) const
7574  {
7575  TElementShape<2, NNODE_1D>::dshape_local(s, psi, dpsids);
7576  }
7577 
7578  /// \short Computer the geometric shape functions, derivatives and
7579  /// second derivatives w.r.t local coordinates at local coordinate s \n
7580  /// d2psids(i,0) = \f$ \partial^2 \psi_j / \partial s_0^2 \f$ \n
7581  /// d2psids(i,1) = \f$ \partial^2 \psi_j / \partial s_1^2 \f$ \n
7582  /// d2psids(i,2) = \f$ \partial^2 \psi_j / \partial s_0 \partial s_1 \f$ \n
7583  inline void d2test_local(const Vector<double>& s,
7584  Shape& psi,
7585  DShape& dpsids,
7586  DShape& d2psids) const
7587  {
7588  TElementShape<2, NNODE_1D>::d2shape_local(s, psi, dpsids, d2psids);
7589  }
7590 
7591  /// \short Build the lower-dimensional FaceElement (an element of type
7592  /// SolidTElement<1,NNODE_1D>). The face index takes three possible values:
7593  /// 0 (Left) s[0] = 0.0
7594  /// 1 (Bottom) s[1] = 0.0
7595  /// 2 (Sloping face) s[0] = 1.0 - s[1]
7596  void build_face_element(const int& face_index,
7597  FaceElement* face_element_pt);
7598  };
7599 
7600  //===========================================================
7601  /// Function to setup geometrical information for lower-dimensional
7602  /// FaceElements (which are of type TElement<1,NNODE_1D>).
7603  //===========================================================
7604  template<unsigned NNODE_1D>
7605  void C1CurvedElement<2, NNODE_1D>::build_face_element(
7606  const int& face_index, FaceElement* face_element_pt)
7607  {
7608  // Build the standard non-solid FaceElement
7609  TElement<2, NNODE_1D>::build_face_element(face_index, face_element_pt);
7610  }
7611 
7612  //=======================================================================
7613  /// Face geometry for the 2D C1CurvedElement elements is exactly
7614  /// the same as for the corresponding TElement. The spatial
7615  /// dimension of the face elements is one lower than that of the
7616  /// bulk element but they have the same number of points
7617  /// along their 1D edges.
7618  //=======================================================================
7619  template<unsigned NNODE_1D>
7620  class FaceGeometry<C1CurvedElement<2, NNODE_1D>>
7621  : public virtual TElement<1, NNODE_1D>
7622  {
7623  public:
7624  /// \short Constructor: Call the constructor for the
7625  /// appropriate lower-dimensional QElement
7626  FaceGeometry() : TElement<1, NNODE_1D>() {}
7627  };
